@startuml
title Select Agent Backend - UML Component Diagram Example

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam wrapWidth 160

actor "H5 Page" as H5
component "LLM Provider" as LLM <<external>>
cloud "Product / Vision /\nMarket Sources" as Sources

package "Select Agent Backend" {
  component "Web Event\nSurfaces" as Web
  component "Response\nBacklog" as Backlog
  component "DeepAgent\nRuntimeStore" as Store
  component "DeepAgent\nRuntime" as Runtime
  component "Select\nTools" as Tools
  database "Storage" as Storage
  component "Adapters" as Adapters

  () "HTTP API" as HttpApi
  () "Tool API" as ToolApi
}

H5 --> HttpApi : calls / streams
HttpApi -- Web

Web --> Backlog : creates turn
Backlog --> Store : event source
Store --> Runtime : run / resume
Runtime --> LLM : model calls

Runtime ..> ToolApi : requires
ToolApi -- Tools

Tools --> Storage : reads / writes facts
Tools --> Adapters : queries sources
Store --> Storage : saves turn state
Adapters --> Sources : fetches

note right of ToolApi
  Provided/required interface
  is what makes this closer
  to a UML component diagram.
end note
@enduml
